thread.title: Five shows you shouldn't miss: October 9 - 15
thread.title_full: Five shows you shouldn't miss: October 9 - 15

author: Scott Ellis
title: Five shows you shouldn't miss: October 9 - 15
text:
Homeland 
Monday, Ten, 9pm 
Claire Danes returns as Carrie Mathison, no longer a member of the CIA, but still very much caught up in international intrigue.
Advertisement The Great Australian Bake-Off 
Tuesday, LifeStyle Food, 8.30pm 
The Australian bakers line up for another season of tackling the toughest cakes and other baked goods around. Delicious viewing!
 
The Ex-PM 
Wednesday, ABC, 8.30pm 
In one of the most timely comedies in years, Shaun Micallef plays a recently ousted Prime Minister desperately looking for relevance.
Please Like Me 
Thursday, ABC, 9,30pm 
With a new house, love and life looking up, Josh Thomas takes us back inside his quirky world. And this time there's baby chickens!
Inside Amy Schumer 
Thursday, ABC2, 10.15pm 
Schumer takes hilarious aim at her own (perceived) shallowness when a plea to God (played by Paul Giamatti) shows just what she's willing to trade to get rid of a STD.
